er amputated. The student was charged with aggravated battery.<ref>[http://www.wsbtv.com/news/news/student-arrested-after-slamming-teachers-hand-door/nFsKH/ Student arrested after slamming teachers hand in door], ''[[WSB-TV]]'' (December 2, 2011)</ref>\n|-\n| December 9, 2011\n| [[Edinburg, Texas]], United States\n| \n|\n| 2 injured\n| Two students were shot after school at Harwell Middle School in Edinburg, Texas while trying out for their school's basketball team. The shooting allegedly occurred from an adult off campus who was apparently shooting on a target range.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/12/12/2-students-shot-wounded-a_n_1144921.html|title=Texas School Shooting: 2 Students Shot, Wounded At Harwell Middle School  |date=December 12, 2011|accessdate=January 31, 2014|work=Huffington Post}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 21, 2011\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| 16-year-old male suspect\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A student at [[Erasmus Hall High School]] was critically injured after being stabbed in the head repeatedly with a pair of scissors. A 16-year-old student was arrested and charged with attempted murder.<ref>{{cite news|title=Teen charged in scissors stabbing of Alfredo Allen at Brooklyn HS had shrink appointment that day, mom says|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/brooklyn/teen-charged-attempted-murder-stabbing-alfredo-allen-brooklyn-school-article-1.994850|accessdate=December 21, 2011|date=September 2, 2013|author=Doyle, John|location=New York|work=Daily News}}</ref> \n|-\n| January 10, 2012\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| 18-year-old male suspect\n| \n| 1 injured\n| One student was shot and injured after another student opened fire at [[North Forest High School]]. The student said that he was being confronted by three other students who were bullying him, and he took out a handgun and fired at them in self-defense. A 16-year-old bystander was unintentionally hit in the leg. The 18-year-old suspect was charged wi