, [[Sri Lanka]]\n| [[LTTE]]\n| 17 dead\n| 14 injured\n| [[Madhu school bus bombing]]. An accidental explosion of a [[claymore mine]] planted by the [[LTTE]] (Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam), a [[Sri Lanka]]n [[Insurgent|militant]] organization, targeting the armed forces, resulted in the deaths of 17 civilians, including 11 children on a school bus in the [[Mannar District]]. Sri Lanka was engaged in a war against LTTE, known for attacking and killing innocent civilians in many occasions throughout a period of more than 30 years of its operation.<ref name=children>{{cite news|author= Reddy, B. Muralidhar|url= http://www.spur.asn.au/Choronology_of_LTTE_Tamil_Tiger_Attacks_on_Passanger_Buses_and_Trains.htm|title= Chronology of LTTE Tamil Tiger Terrorist's recent attacks on passenger buses and trains|accessdate= 2008-05-09|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080720103635/http://www.spur.asn.au/Choronology_of_LTTE_Tamil_Tiger_Attacks_on_Passanger_Buses_and_Trains.htm|archivedate= 2008-07-20}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 4, 2008\n| [[Memphis, Tennessee]], United States\n| \n|\n| 1 injured\n| At Hamilton High School, a 16-year-old student was shot in the leg during an argument with another student over rap music. The victim's injury was not life-threatening.<ref>{{cite web| title = Police investigate shooting inside classroom at Hamilton High|publisher= [[WMCTV]]| date = February 4, 2008| url = http://www.wmctv.com/story/7818497/police-investigate-shooting-inside-classroom-at-hamilton-high| first = Kontji| last = Anthony| accessdate = August 31, 2013| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140302022256/http://www.wmctv.com/story/7818497/police-investigate-shooting-inside-classroom-at-hamilton-high| archive-date = 2014-03-02| url-status = dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 12, 2008\n| [[Oxnard]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Brandon David McInerney, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old [[Lawrence Fobes King]] was shot in the head twice by 14-year-old 