kull. In 2012, Treacy was found guilty of attempted first-degree murder and was sentenced to 20 years of prison and 10 years of probation.<ref>{{cite news|author=Anderson, Curt|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/10/22/wayne-treacy-sentenced-josie-lou-ratley-beating_n_2000504.html|title=Wayne Treacy Sentenced In Josie Lou Ratley School Stomping Case (VIDEO)|work=[[The Huffington Post]] |date=October 22, 2012 |accessdate=July 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Chang, Daniel|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/2012/07/10/2890170/surgeon-in-treacy-trial-ratley.html|title=Surgeon in Treacy trial: \u2018Ratley lucky to be alive\u2019 |newspaper=[[Miami Herald]] |date=July 10, 2012 |accessdate=July 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Anderson, Curt|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/07/16/wayne-treacy-guilty-convicted-verdict-josie-lou-ratley_n_1677103.html|title=Wayne Treacy Guilty In Beating Of Josie Lou Ratley At Deerfield Beach Middle School (VIDEO)|work=[[The Huffington Post]] |date=July 16, 2012 |accessdate=July 16, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 30, 2010\n| [[Oshawa]],<br>[[Ontario]]<br>Canada\n| Jacques Amakon, 18\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Michael McDonald, a 16-year-old student at [[Monsignor Paul Dwyer Catholic High School]], was stabbed to death at a bus stop across from the school. Jacques Amakon, an 18-year-old student, was arrested after the stabbing and charged with [[second-degree murder]]. It was reported that the two students were involved in a dispute.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/787988--teens-watch-as-schoolmate-stabbed-to-death-in-oshawa |title=Teens watch as schoolmate stabbed to death in Oshawa |publisher=Thestar.com |date= March 31, 2010|accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=Toronto |first1=Tamara |last1=Baluja |first2=Carola |last2=Vyhnak}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citytv.com/toronto/citynews/news/local/article/73412--teen-dies-after-stabbing-near-oshawa-school |title=Teen Dies After Stabbing Near Oshawa School