24/580433745/a-look-at-all-11-school-shootings-that-took-place-in-the-first-23-days-of-2018|title=A Look at all 11 school shooting that took place in the first 23 days of 2018|work=[[MPRNews]]|access-date=January 25, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|January 23, 2018}}\n|[[Benton, Kentucky]], US\n| Gabe Parker, 15 (charged) \n| 2 dead\n| 18 injured\n|[[Marshall County High School shooting]]: A 15-year-old male student shot 16 people in the lobby at Marshall County High School and caused non-gunshot injuries to 4 others. Two 15-year-old students died: one killed at the scene, another died of wounds at [[Vanderbilt University Medical Center|Vanderbilt Medical Center]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/kentucky-shooting-marshall-county-high-school-students-shot-today-2018-01-23-live-updates/|title=Kentucky school shooting: 2 dead, 15 more shot at Marshall County High School -- live updates|website=cbsnews.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/one-dead-after-shooting-kentucky-high-school-multiple-victims-reported-n840171|title=Two dead, suspect in custody after shooting at Kentucky high school|website=nbcnews.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/01/23/us/kentucky-high-school-shooting/index.html|title=Kentucky school shooting: 2 students killed, 18 injured|author1=Holly Yan |author2=AnneClaire Stapleton |author3=Paul P. Murphy|website=cnn.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|February 14, 2018}}\n|[[Parkland, Florida]], US\n| Nikolas Cruz, 19\n| 17 dead\n| 17 injured\n|[[Stoneman Douglas High School shooting]]\n|-\n|-\n|{{Dts|March 20,2018}}\n|[[Great Mills, Maryland]], US\n| Austin Rollins, 17\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n| A 17-year-old male student, armed with a handgun, shot and fatally injured a female student (with whom he had a prior relationship), then began firing at random people in the school, wounding a male student. The suspect shot himself in the head fatally after engaging with the school's SRO, while the 